text: Pseudophilautus auratus is a frog. It lives in Sri Lanka. It lives in forests where the branches of the trees meet and look like a roof. It lives in Sinharaja World Heritage Site and Kanneliya Forest. People have seen it between 513 and 1270 meters above sea level. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Pseudophilautus auratus
